How do you make an LWC available in Lightning App Builder?
Companies that asked this: Salesforce, TCS, Accenture, Deloitte, IBM, Infosys, Capgemini



Answer:

To make an LWC component available in Lightning App Builder, you need to configure the .js-meta.xml file with specific settings. This configuration file tells Salesforce where and how the component can be used.

Essential Requirements:

isExposed: true - Makes component visible in App Builder

targets - Defines where component can be placed

apiVersion - Must be 45.0 or higher (required in Spring '25)

targetConfigs - Adds configurable properties (optional)"

Basic Configuration Example:

xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<LightningComponentBundle xmlns="http://soap.sforce.com/2006/04/metadata">
    <apiVersion>58.0</apiVersion>
    <isExposed>true</isExposed>
    
    <targets>
        <target>lightning__RecordPage</target>
        <target>lightning__AppPage</target>
        <target>lightning__HomePage</target>
    </targets>
</LightningComponentBundle>
Common Target Options:

lightning__RecordPage - Record detail pages

lightning__AppPage - Custom app pages

lightning__HomePage - Home page

lightning__Tab - Custom tabs

lightning__FlowScreen - Flow screens

lightning__UtilityBar - Utility bar

Interview Tips:

Emphasize isExposed="true" as the key requirement

Mention different targets for different page types

Show understanding of configurable properties with @api

Give real examples of components that benefit from configuration

Note API version requirement (shows current knowledge)
